say you migrate from key A to key B.

key A signs a message that says "I've moved to key B".

ok cool, now I'm using key B.

key A is compromised, and signs a new message "I've moved to key C", where C is also attacker-controlled.

Without knowing event order, a 3rd party can't pick between B and C.
